00:00:47.600 --> 00:00:49.715
we were able to start working on our application.

00:00:49.715 --> 00:00:52.325
What we did is we ran Docker locally and we

00:00:52.325 --> 00:00:55.280
verified that we can install bash and run bash

00:00:55.280 --> 00:00:57.859
and get a Ubuntu running and then verify that

00:00:57.859 --> 00:01:01.344
those Python packages were actually installed in that container.

00:01:01.344 --> 00:01:05.090
Then the final step was to go through and take a customized

00:01:05.090 --> 00:01:06.350
container that we built,

00:01:06.349 --> 00:01:10.250
deployed it to Amazon ECR and then verify that we're able

00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:11.855
to actually upload that,

00:01:11.855 --> 00:01:14.590
and it's now living in our Container Registry.

00:01:14.590 --> 00:01:17.990
What's powerful about this is it now allows us to deploy

00:01:17.989 --> 00:01:21.259
that container into thousands of nodes and actually reach

00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:25.850
a scale and also a reliability that previously didn't exist before

00:01:25.849 --> 00:01:31.509
